Package csv

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CSVParser
    CSVParser class reads input from a CSV file one line at a time and sets various attributes Uses the attributes stored in CSVParser object to fill the EnrollmentData class
    EnrollmentData
    EnrollmentData class where one object represents a table containing all data for different countries and returns it
    GDPIndicator
    GDPIndicator class extends the abstract class Indicator Processes and returns the String representation of the GDP per capita data
    Indicator
    Indicator abstract class manages different data we read from one or more input files by taking advantage of inheritance to store different indicators in the same data structure
    SchoolEnrollmentIndicator
    SchoolEnrollmentIndicator class extends the abstract class Indicator Processes and returns the String representation of the data categories net percentage of children in enrolled in primary school and net percentage of children enrolled in secondary school
    TestIndicators
    Tests the CSVParser class, which reads input from a CSV file.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    IndicatorType
    IndicatorType enum class
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidFileFormatException
    InvalidFileFormatException class extends java.io.IOException and throws an object of this type when a class wants to indicate that the format of the file is not valid
